Zooming an Image

This example illustrates the use of zoomImage to zoom in and out of an image.
First, display the image.
A = imread("roses-se.jpg");
imshow(A)
Next, zoom in by a factor of 2.
zoomImage(2)
Zoom in again by a factor of 5.
zoomImage(5)
The axes and figure size did not change, so only the center portion of the image is visible.
Zoom out by specifying a zoom factor less than 1.
zoomImage(1/20)
